article.description: Justin Hurtt scored 20 points and Jordan Clarkson had 19 points to lead Tulsa to an 80-63 victory over Cal State Northridge on Sunday in the 76 Classic.
article.headline: Cal State Northridge falls to Tulsa in 76 Classic
article.linkText: Cal State Northridge falls to Tulsa in 76 Classic
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. -- Justin Hurtt scored 20 points and Jordan Clarkson had 19 points to lead Tulsa to an 80-63 victory over Cal State Northridge on Sunday in the 76 Classic. Joe Richard added 10 points and six rebounds for the Golden Hurricane (4-2), who shot 50 percent and won for the fourth time in five games. Lenny Daniel had 24 points, eight rebounds and two blocks for the Matadors (2-4). Vinnie McGhee added 15 points. Tulsa center Steven Idlet left the game with 9:24 to play after landing hard on the floor following a missed slam dunk and did not return.
